<br>
Typical MA,<br>
<br>
Tank-- Need haste, Need Damage shield, need symbol, hero, talisman of kragg, shroud, STR, DEX, AGI, MR, SoW, Natureskin. . .<br>
<br>
During the battle, they have clerics casting complete heal on them.  A warrior after CH is 100% good to go, the casters are still medding of course.<br>
<br>
So after all this, you are still amazed they outdamage a magician?  I'm certainly not.<br>
<br>
Magicians are still out there soloing blues at level 56.  Ask warriors how often they solo.  Ask warriors what a pain it is to not have bind and gate.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of issues involved in &quot;class balancing&quot;.  I don't feel that ultimate raid dmg vs. high-end uber-mob is the only way to guage strength.<br>
<br>
<br>
The things I don't like?<br>
<br>
Int caster research.  Wisdom caster don't have to do it, why?  You would think a spell as powerful as Complete heal would at least need some researching.<br>
<br>
When I hit level 29+ and spend hours on spell research and spending money on new spells, the melee character goes into his guildmaster and hits &quot;train&quot; for his new skill and goes back out to hunt 60 seconds later.<br>
<br>
Melee get the benefit of a spell like complete heal, where a nearly dead warrior is suddenly back to 100% health, add a STA refresh and he is basically unscratched from the battle.<br>
<br>
What about complete manadump?  (Ok that's what necros and mod rods are for, but go with this).  Give a spell to hybrids that dumps all their mana to the caster, they get buffs all the time, they can give some back for a change <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
