<br>
If you really want to have a comparison done.  Lets take 60 rogue with only SELF buffs vs. a magician with only SELF buffs and his epic pet with mage only buffs.  Then take a parse of the 2 classes and compare.  Make sure mage is FoM, and neither class can have any buffs or heals of any kind during the battle.<br>
<br>
While everyone continues to discuss class balancing issues, nobody really gives those 60 rogues credit for the long journey to get there.  They only complain about the high damage they do now compared to us.<br>
<br>
We have pets that cost a couple silver and tank better than rogues<br>
We have bind/gate.<br>
We have invis and levitate for traveling.<br>
We have ultravision spell<br>
We never buy food or water<br>
We can carry tons of weight in summoned bags<br>
We can solo Hill giants at level 44, ask rogues how many they solo'd<br>
<br>
I remember sitting in OoT doing Seafuries with another mage, shaman and rogue.  After we were done, waved goodbye to the rogue and all gated back to Freeport while he waited 15 minutes for the boat and another 15-20 for the boat ride (boat went to BB first, then back to FP).<br>
<br>
I just feel if we are going to do all of this class balancing talk, we need to remember what those classes have to put up with during the 1-50+ stage of life as well as the rest.<br>
<br>
<br>
